<reference id="class_rtcsurfaceview">
    <title><ph keyref="RtcSurfaceView"/></title>
    <shortdesc id="short"><ph id="shortdesc" props="rn">RtcSurfaceView class.</ph></shortdesc>
    <refbody>
        <section id="detailed_desc" deliveryTarget="details" otherprops="no-title" props="rn">
            <p props="rn">This class is used for rendering:
                <ul>
                    <li>Android: Corresponds to the native SurfaceView of the Android system.</li>
                    <li>iOS: Corresponds to the native UIView of the iOS system.</li>
                </ul><ph>To ensure rendering works, perform the following operations before calling this component depending on whether you have joined a channel:</ph>
                <ul>
                    <li>If not joined: Call <xref keyref="startPreview2"/> first, then call <xref keyref="enableVideo"/>.</li>
                    <li>If joined: Start capture first, then call <xref keyref="enableVideo"/>.</li>
                </ul><ph>Related references:</ph>
                <ul>
                    <li><xref keyref="RtcSurfaceViewProps"/></li>
                    <li><xref keyref="RtcRendererViewProps"/></li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </section>
    </refbody>
</reference>